org.jlab.coda.emu

Class EmuDataPath

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jlab.coda.emu.EmuDataPath

  • public class EmuDataPath
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents data flow through connected EMU modules. It's constructed in 2 stages. First, the EMU config file is parsed and a linked list of Modules from module names is made. Later when EmuModule objects are constructed by the Emu, they are placed in the existing list so proper distribution of run control commands can be made.
    Author:
    timmer

      • addModuleName

        public boolean addModuleName(java.lang.String name,
                             java.lang.String inputFifo,
                             java.lang.String outputFifo)
        Add a module to the data path. This method does not add an EmuModule object, but only the module name and any input and output fifo names. Any associated EmuModule is attached later with a call to associateModule(EmuModule).
        Parameters:
        name - name of module to create and add
        inputFifo - name of any input fifo, else null
        outputFifo - name of any output fifo, else null
        Returns:
        true if module added, else false
